Italian Deputy Prime Minister and Interior Minister visit the Rome's largest cattery located in the Verano Cemetary, as part of the initiative against animal cruelty, on July 17, 2019 in Rome, Italy. Photo: VCGAn Italian couple survived a landslide that caused their house to collapse after being woken by their cats, giving them time to escape, media reported."My wife got up because Simba and Mose, our cats, were making a noise and woke us up," Claudio Piana told the local newspaper, as violent storms lashed northern Italy, forcing dozens of people seperate from their homes.Piana and his wife Sabrina Pellegrini had gone to bed at home on Monday night as fierce rains across the Liguria region saw rivers burst their banks, washed away a bridge and sparked landslides. One such landslide had damaged the house's foundations.The couple rushed out to the car, but found themselves trapped by a sea of mud. They were rescued by firefighters."Now we have nothing. The firefighters said we can never go back into the house," Piana added."At least Simba and Mose survived." 
